LIBRARY GARAGE, a Corporation; Appellant, v. GENERAL PETROLEUM CORPORATION, OF CALIFORNIA, a Corporation, Appellee. No. 6979. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 7, 1933. Reynolds, Flegel & Smith, Arthur S. Vosburg, and F. P. Keenan, all of Portland, Or., for appellant. A. L. Weil, of San Francisco, Cal., and Bert S. Gooding and Wood, Montague, Matthiessen & Rankin, all of Portland, Or., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and MACK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of record, briefs and oral arguments made by counsel, ordered decree of District Court affirmed.
